  "text": "Understanding other predictive factors for the dose-effect relationship may also ensure a more tailored IRM recession for TED patients. Smoking and orbital radiotherapy are representative factors involved in the aggravation of strabismus in TED patients. Smoking increases thyroid autoantibodies, causes severe orbital inflammation by inducing hypoxia, and decreases the response to medical treatment [CITATION_1] . Orbital radiotherapy is used for reducing orbital inflammation in TED patients but occasionally leads to excessive orbital fibrosis [CITATION_2] . However, the correlation between the dose-effect relationship and these factors has not been elucidated.",
  "correct_citation": {
